        "title": "3. `store.py` â€” core dedup logic, no integration test exists at all",
        "content": "\n**Untested:** `Store.__init__`/schema creation, `_migrate` (additive column), `diff` (new/changed/unchanged branches), `get_meta`/`set_meta` (insert + upsert), `added_since` (ordering, boundary), `count`.\n\n**Edge cases missed:**\n- `diff` called twice with identical jobs â†’ second call returns `([], [])`, only `last_seen` updates.\n- `diff` with a job whose material fields changed â†’ lands in `changed`, `content_hash` updated in DB.\n- `_migrate`: opening a pre-existing DB file that lacks `salary_range` column (simulate by creating table without it, then reopening with `Store`).\n- `added_since` strict `>` boundary â€” a row with `first_seen == ts` must be excluded.\n- `set_meta` upsert path â€” set twice, confirm second value wins, no duplicate row.\n- Context manager (`__enter__`/`__exit__`) actually closes the connection.\n\n```python\nimport sqlite3\nimport pytest\nfrom store import Store\nfrom models import Job\n\n@pytest.fixture\ndef store(tmp_path):\n    with Store(tmp_path / \"test.db\") as s:\n        yield s\n\ndef _job(ext_id=\"1\", title=\"Engineer\", **kw):\n    return Job(source=\"greenhouse\", company=\"acme\", external_id=ext_id, title=title, url=\"u\", **kw)\n\ndef test_diff_first_seen_is_new(store):\n    new, changed = store.diff([_job()])\n    assert len(new) == 1 and changed == []\n\ndef test_diff_unchanged_second_run_produces_no_new_or_changed(store):\n    store.diff([_job()])\n    new, changed = store.diff([_job()])\n    assert new == [] and changed == []\n\ndef test_diff_material_change_lands_in_changed(store):\n    store.diff([_job(title=\"Engineer\")])\n    new, changed = store.diff([_job(title=\"Senior Engineer\")])\n    assert new == [] and len(changed) == 1\n\ndef test_added_since_excludes_equal_timestamp(store):\n    store.diff([_job()])\n    row = store.conn.execute(\"SELECT first_seen FROM jobs\").fetchone()\n    assert store.added_since(row[\"first_seen\"]) == []\n\ndef test_set_meta_upsert_overwrites(store):\n    store.set_meta(\"last_scan\", \"a\")\n    store.set_meta(\"last_scan\", \"b\")\n    assert store.get_meta(\"last_scan\") == \"b\"\n    assert store.conn.execute(\"SELECT COUNT(*) FROM meta\").fetchone()[0] == 1\n\ndef test_migrate_adds_salary_range_to_legacy_db(tmp_path):\n    path = tmp_path / \"legacy.db\"\n    conn = sqlite3.connect(path)\n    conn.executescript(\"\"\"\n        CREATE TABLE jobs (key TEXT PRIMARY KEY, source TEXT, company TEXT,\n          external_id TEXT, title TEXT, url TEXT, location TEXT, department TEXT,\n          employment_type TEXT, posted_at TEXT, content_hash TEXT,\n          first_seen TEXT, last_seen TEXT);\n        CREATE TABLE meta (k TEXT PRIMARY KEY, v TEXT NOT NULL);\n    \"\"\")\n    conn.commit(); conn.close()\n    with Store(path) as s:\n        cols = {r[\"name\"] for r in s.conn.execute(\"PRAGMA table_info(jobs)\")}\n        assert \"salary_range\" in cols\n```\n\n---\n\n",
