        "title": "5. `pipeline.py`",
        "content": "\n**Untested:** `load_config` (defaults, missing keys), `run` (dry_run branch, normal branch), `run_sync`.\n\n**Edge cases missed:**\n- `load_config`: minimal YAML with only `sources:` set still gets `filters={}`, `db=\"jobs.db\"`, `concurrency=8` defaults.\n- `run(dry_run=True)`: must **not** touch the `Store` at all (currently instantiated only in the `else` branch â€” a regression here would start writing dedup state during dry runs).\n- `run`: return dict shape (`matched`/`new`/`changed`) under normal + dry-run paths.\n- These need `fetch_all`, `filter_jobs`, `Store`, `dispatch` mocked/monkeypatched â€” this is really an integration test of the orchestration wiring.\n\n```python\nimport pytest\nimport yaml\nimport pipeline\nfrom models import Job\n\ndef test_load_config_applies_defaults(tmp_path):\n    cfg_path = tmp_path / \"sources.yaml\"\n    cfg_path.write_text(yaml.dump({\"sources\": [{\"ats\": \"greenhouse\", \"company\": \"acme\"}]}))\n    cfg = pipeline.load_config(cfg_path)\n    assert cfg[\"filters\"] == {}\n    assert cfg[\"db\"] == \"jobs.db\"\n    assert cfg[\"concurrency\"] == 8\n\n@pytest.mark.asyncio\nasync def test_run_dry_run_never_touches_store(tmp_path, monkeypatch):\n    cfg_path = tmp_path / \"sources.yaml\"\n    cfg_path.write_text(yaml.dump({\"sources\": []}))\n\n    async def fake_fetch_all(sources, concurrency): \n        return [Job(source=\"s\", company=\"c\", external_id=\"1\", title=\"T\", url=\"u\")]\n    monkeypatch.setattr(pipeline, \"fetch_all\", fake_fetch_all)\n    monkeypatch.setattr(pipeline, \"filter_jobs\", lambda jobs, rules: jobs)\n\n    class ExplodingStore:\n        def __init__(self, *a, **k): raise AssertionError(\"Store must not open during dry_run\")\n    monkeypatch.setattr(pipeline, \"Store\", ExplodingStore)\n\n    result = await pipeline.run(cfg_path, dry_run=True)\n    assert result == {\"matched\": 1, \"new\": 0, \"changed\": 0}\n```\n\n---\n\n",
