        "title": "7. `agent.py`",
        "content": "\n**Untested:** `cmd_db_new` (watermark truncation logic, first-run window), `cmd_db_mark` (validation), `_normalize_ats`, `_chrome_bin` (discovery order), `run_claude`/`main` (arg routing).\n\n**Edge cases missed â€” these are the subtlest, highest-value gaps in the whole codebase:**\n- `cmd_db_new`'s truncation logic: the comment explains it truncates only at `first_seen` group boundaries (never splits a batch sharing one timestamp). This needs a test with rows spanning 3 distinct `first_seen` timestamps where the limit falls mid-group â€” assert the whole group is excluded, `truncated=True`, and `watermark` is the *last complete* group's timestamp, not a partial one.\n- `cmd_db_new` first-run (`marker is None`): `since` computed from `--since-days`, `first_run=True` in output.\n- `cmd_db_mark`: rejects a non-ISO watermark string (returns 2, doesn't write), accepts `--now`, requires either `watermark` or `--now` (returns 2 if neither).\n- `_normalize_ats`: replacements apply inside body text but **not** inside tags/`<style>`/`<script>` â€” needs a fixture HTML with an em-dash inside a tag attribute and inside `<style>` to confirm it's left untouched, plus one in visible text that IS replaced. `counts` dict correctly tallies occurrences per rule label.\n- `_chrome_bin`: `CHROME_PATH` env var takes precedence when it exists; falls back through `shutil.which` candidates; falls back to hardcoded app paths; exits via `sys.exit` when nothing found (test via `monkeypatch` faking `shutil.which` to return `None` and `Path.exists` to return `False`).\n- `main`/argv routing: `db-new`/`db-mark`/`pdf-render` subcommands dispatch correctly; bare `agent.py` â†’ `interactive=True`; `agent.py scan` â†’ non-interactive with `mode_words=[\"scan\"]`; `agent.py scan -i` â†’ interactive; mode words correctly stop at the first flag-like token, rest passed through as `extra`.\n\n```python\nimport pytest\nfrom datetime import datetime, timezone\nimport agent\n\ndef test_normalize_ats_skips_style_and_tag_but_replaces_body_text():\n    html = '<style>content: \"\\u2014\";</style><p title=\"\\u2014\">He said \\u2014 hi</p>'\n    out, counts = agent._normalize_ats(html)\n    assert 'content: \"\\u2014\"' in out          # inside <style>, untouched\n    assert 'title=\"\\u2014\"' in out              # inside a tag attribute, untouched\n    assert \"He said - hi\" in out                # body text, replaced\n    assert counts[\"em-dash\"] == 1\n\ndef test_cmd_db_mark_rejects_non_iso(capsys):\n    rc = agent.cmd_db_mark([\"not-a-timestamp\"])\n    assert rc == 2\n    assert \"not an ISO timestamp\" in capsys.readouterr().err\n\ndef test_cmd_db_mark_requires_watermark_or_now(capsys):\n    rc = agent.cmd_db_mark([])\n    assert rc == 2\n\ndef test_cmd_db_new_truncates_at_group_boundary(tmp_path, monkeypatch, capsys):\n    from store import Store\n    from models import Job\n    cfg = tmp_path / \"sources.yaml\"\n    cfg.write_text(f\"sources: []\\ndb: {tmp_path / 'j.db'}\\n\")\n    with Store(tmp_path / \"j.db\") as s:\n        # simulate 3 pipeline runs -> 3 distinct first_seen groups of 2 rows each\n        for batch in range(3):\n            jobs = [Job(source=\"s\", company=\"c\", external_id=f\"{batch}-{i}\",\n                        title=\"T\", url=\"u\") for i in range(2)]\n            s.diff(jobs)\n    rc = agent.cmd_db_new([\"-c\", str(cfg), \"--limit\", \"3\"])  # limit falls mid-3rd-group\n    out = json.loads(capsys.readouterr().out)\n    assert out[\"truncated\"] is True\n    assert out[\"count\"] == 4   # only first two complete groups kept\n```\n\n*(Note: this last test needs the three `diff()` calls to actually get distinct `first_seen` timestamps â€” the current `_now()`/`datetime.now()` calls are at second resolution, so this test will need either `monkeypatch` on `store.datetime` or a tiny real sleep between batches to avoid flakiness. Worth flagging as a design consideration: `cmd_db_new`'s correctness depends on distinguishable `first_seen` values, which is a fragile assumption for tests and possibly for tight back-to-back pipeline runs too.)*\n\n---\n\n",
        "level": 3
      },
